-- British Open Play Resumes After Hour-Long Break Because of High Winds
-- Christopher Elser
-- 2010-07-16T14:49:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/british-open-play-resumes-after-hour-long-break-because-of-high-winds.html

          
          
             British Open play restarted after an
hour’s delay because of high winds at St. Andrews in Scotland.  
 South Africa’s Louis Oosthuizen shot a 5-under-par 67 to
take a three-stroke lead over Rory McIlroy in the second round
of the golf tournament. Tiger Woods is on the course.  
          
          


  


        